Package: pi-wayvnc-macos
Version: @VERSION@
Section: admin
Priority: optional
Architecture: @ARCH@
Maintainer: Andrian Budantsov <AndrianBdn@users.noreply.github.com>
Homepage: https://github.com/AndrianBdn/pi-wayvnc-macos
Depends: wayvnc (>= 0.9.1-1+rpt5), systemd, @SHLIB_DEPS@
Description: wayvnc fork with DES VNC-Auth for macOS Screen Sharing
 Drop-in override for the Raspberry Pi wayvnc package that adds support for
 VNC security type 2 (DES authentication) so that macOS Screen Sharing.app
 can connect to a Raspberry Pi Wayland desktop.
 .
 Installs isolated binaries and libraries under /opt/pi-wayvnc-macos/ and
 overrides wayvnc.service via a systemd drop-in. Does not replace any files
 owned by the stock wayvnc or libneatvnc0 packages, so apt remove cleanly
 reverts to stock VNC.
 .
 SECURITY: DES VNC-Auth is cryptographically broken (8-character maximum,
 weak hash). Use only on trusted networks or behind an SSH tunnel.
